      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "This actually doesn&#39;t matter in most cases, <a href=\"http://www.codinghorror.com/blog/2009/01/the-sad-tragedy-of-micro-optimization-theater.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Coding Horror&#39;s Jeff Atwood made a blog post about this particular sort of micro-optimization</a>. Always do metrics before making claims such as &quot;don&#39;t do <code>string + string</code>&quot;."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 97092,
        "reputation" : 306,
        "user_id" : 263554,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e71e5a02a04df8bf81da40af3eba2593?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Lajcik",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/263554/lajcik"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 6,
      "creation_date" : 1355754139,
      "post_id" : 13719364,
      "comment_id" : 19180623,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I&#39;d say that Jeff&#39;s article may be a bit off since it only touches on execution time. String concatenation in Java is not only about execution speed but also how much garbage you leave in memory for the GC to clean, which may result in the GC running more often. This might or might not be an issue depending on your environment and configuration."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 29057,
        "reputation" : 2614,
        "user_id" : 78212,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 67,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/xsWZ1.png?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Richard Watson",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/78212/richard-watson"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 8,
      "creation_date" : 1357814907,
      "post_id" : 13719364,
      "comment_id" : 19784534,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Lajcik, I suspect that&#39;s pre-optimization for all cases except those who really do a lot of string manipulation. The StringBuffer is an anti-pattern for minor concatenation requirements. In many cases I&#39;d rather have readable String1 + separator + String2 than the abovementioned multi-line example. Besides, I&#39;d suggest testing whether memory &amp; GC is impacted positively by adding the SB. In many cases I&#39;d guess it isn&#39;t. If it&#39;s not worth testing, it&#39;s probably pre-optimizing and I&#39;d focus on readability."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 129401,
        "reputation" : 2520,
        "user_id" : 327961,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 50,
