      "creation_date" : 1368622128,
      "post_id" : 13719364,
      "comment_id" : 23800384,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Doing a String1 + String2 is the same as doing new StringBuilder(String1).append(String2) in modern compilers, so there is no optimization at all for a one liner string concat. StringBuilder is generaly worth it only in loops or recursive methods. But anyway, this might be out of the scope of the original question."
